originalText.text: This is a scam shipping company. I’m out $200 coz they wanted me to insure  a delivery. They will give you a fake tracking number to make you think your package is on its way. I never got my package.  It’s not legit. Beware!!!! Total SCAM!!!

originalText.text: This is LITERALLY the ABSOLUTE WORST shipping company. I placed an order for winter clothes for my 1 year old from Zara and i received a tracking number from TForce. It was delivered the same day I got the tracking number from Zara but there was no communication about the delivery. There was no call, no text, no one rang my bell. And worst of all, they left my package OUTSIDE of my apartment building's door, where anyone could (and clearly someone did) take it. When I called, I spoke to a rep (Rahul B.) and he basically told me that it is not the deliverers responsibility to notify me that my package was delivered. I don't even understand that logic...Zara needs to do better. UPS/Fedex would never.

originalText.text:
Five stars if you want your package lost or late!

Multiple times amazon has blessed me with Dynamex's shipping.  I say blessed because it is so horrible and insane the only way to track your shipment is through prayer.

I've had packages marked "Delivered" and there was no delivery made.  Maybe a neighbor took it?  Nope.  I went to every neighbor in the apartment and asked, not a single delivery was made with my name.

Other times, I've had packages delivered to the office below.  Not because it was a safe delivery place but because they didn't read the apartment number one the package and must have thought "This is good enough, right?".

Now, I'm dealing with an attempted delivery, that was marked unsafe to deliver.  So I guess when I'm waiting at home all day it's not a safe delivery?  No delivery attempted, obviously.  It's been three days and not another "attempt".

If you want something lost forever don't throw it in the ocean, use Dynamex.  You know it will never be seen again once it's in their hands.

originalText.text: Super shady delivery company. My Amazon order went missing for five days so I called customer service, which I think is in South Asia somewhere. They told me the address was incorrect, which was not true, but confirmed details anyway. Then the next day they updated Amazon stating it had been delivered five days earlier. The thing is their rep confirmed to me the day before it had not been delivered yet. No idea why Amazon use these thieves

originalText.text: Amazon used this carrier to deliver my package that was supposed to be delivered yesterday. I received a notification that they attempted to deliver my package but ran into a problem. Status was updated this morning to say that it would be delivered today by 8pm. I received yet another notification this afternoon that they attempted to deliver my package at 3:47 but they ran into yet another problem. What problem? I do not live in a building I do not need to buzz them in. I live in a residential area where all they needed to do was open my gate climb 4 steps and leave my package on the porch. I have cameras so I know that there was  NO ATTEMPT 2 days in a row. I have never heard of this company and I do not know why Amazon continues to use these mediocre companies that have less than 2 star ratings to deliver packages to their loyal customers.
